# TD1_2

## Exercise 2

#### Q1. Create a variable x and assign it the short text piri pimpin
```
x = "piri pimpin"
```
#### Q2. Display the value of this variable
```
echo $x
```
#### Q3. Add to this value the following text piri pimpon
```
x="$x piri pimpon"
```
It should contain the following : piri pimpim piri pimpon

4. Create a folder named my_programs, then enter into that folder
```
echo $x
```
5. Create a script named pilou that displays pilou pilou
```
echo $x
```
6. Run this script
```
echo $x
```
7. Make this script executable
```
echo $x
```
8. Run the script by writting its name only
```
echo $x
```
9. Programs called from the terminal are usually found thanks to a variable
named PATH
```
echo $x
```
Display the content of the variable PATH
```
echo $x
```
10. Add the path of your current location to the global variable PATH
```
echo $x
```
11. When you are sure of the result, export it
```
echo $x
```
12. Go to your home directory
```
echo $x
```
13. Run your script by writting its name only
```
echo $x
```
14. Change the value of the PATH in the .profile file in order to make it
permanent
```
echo $x
```
15. Create a new shell and run your script using its name only
```
echo $x
```
